Have you ever gazed at both sides of your face in the mirror, trying to determine your “best” side? 

Well, mine is my left profile!

Research suggest that poser’s left cheek tend to exhibit a greater intensity of emotion, which observers find more aesthetically pleasing. It’s part of a study called emotional lateralization – the idea that the two sides of our brains process and control emotion differently.

🌟 Top Reasons Your Acne or Acne Scars Aren’t Improving:
🔹 Wrong diagnosis – Not all bumps are acne!
🔹 Skipping sunscreen – UV rays worsen scars & pigmentation ☀️
🔹 DIY overload – Too many products = irritated skin 🧴🚫
🔹 Deep pigmentation – You may need Q-Switch Laser or Peels
🔹 PCOS or hormonal imbalance – Inside issues show up on the skin
🔹 Post-acne care ignored – Treating acne is only 50% of the job!
🔹 No expert follow-up – Skin needs consistent, guided care 💆‍♀️
